âœ… Implementation of Function Template
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Aim:

To implement a function template in C++ that allows the same function to work with different data types.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Algorithm:

1. Start the program.
2. Declare a function template using the syntax:
template <class T>
3. Define a generic function (e.g., swapValues(), add(), etc.) that works for any datatype T.
4. In the main() function:
Call the template function with different types such as int, float, and char.
5. Display the result of each function call.
6. Stop the program.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Program (C++ Function Template Implementation):

Example: Function Template to Swap Two Values

#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

// Function Template
template <class T>
void swapValues(T &x, T &y) {
    T temp = x;
    x = y;
    y = temp;
}

int main() {
    int a = 10, b = 20;
    float p = 3.5, q = 7.8;
    char c1 = 'A', c2 = 'Z';

    cout << "Before swapping:" << endl;
    cout << "a = " << a << ", b = " << b << endl;
    cout << "p = " << p << ", q = " << q << endl;
    cout << "c1 = " << c1 << ", c2 = " << c2 << endl;

    // Calling template function
    swapValues(a, b);
    swapValues(p, q);
    swapValues(c1, c2);

    cout << "\nAfter swapping:" << endl;
    cout << "a = " << a << ", b = " << b << endl;
    cout << "p = " << p << ", q = " << q << endl;
    cout << "c1 = " << c1 << ", c2 = " << c2 << endl;

    return 0;
}
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Output:

Before swapping:
a = 10, b = 20
p = 3.5, q = 7.8
c1 = A, c2 = Z

After swapping:
a = 20, b = 10
p = 7.8, q = 3.5
c1 = Z, c2 = A
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Result:

Thus, the function template is successfully implemented in C++ and demonstrated using different data types such as int, float, and char.
